1
00:00:00,110 --> 00:00:01,260
Hi guys, it's Mark.

2
00:00:01,260 --> 00:00:02,890
So today I'm gonna be talking

3
00:00:02,890 --> 00:00:05,010
about how passive income allowed me

4
00:00:05,010 --> 00:00:07,930
to go from a normal teen
working a nine to five job

5
00:00:07,930 --> 00:00:10,210
to becoming a millionaire in my twenties.

6
00:00:10,210 --> 00:00:12,700
I'm gonna be sharing with
you all the strategies

7
00:00:12,700 --> 00:00:14,030
that actually worked for me,

8
00:00:14,030 --> 00:00:15,850
as well as lots of my mistakes,

9
00:00:15,850 --> 00:00:17,760
so hopefully you can do even better.

10
00:00:17,760 --> 00:00:20,690
This is the story of how I
went from a small English town

11
00:00:20,690 --> 00:00:23,280
to the rolling hills of San Francisco

12
00:00:23,280 --> 00:00:25,770
and the bustling city of Shanghai, China,

13
00:00:25,770 --> 00:00:28,680
including all the challenges
I faced along the way.

14
00:00:28,680 --> 00:00:30,800
Who knows, by watching
this video to the end,

15
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:33,220
it may open up a new pathway for you

16
00:00:33,220 --> 00:00:34,740
that you might wanna walk down.

17
00:00:34,740 --> 00:00:37,850
You'll also find out why
a simple desk like this

18
00:00:37,850 --> 00:00:39,490
can mean so much to me.

19
00:00:39,490 --> 00:00:40,460
If that sounds good,

20
00:00:40,460 --> 00:00:42,480
then give that like button a smash

21
00:00:42,480 --> 00:00:45,710
and strap in for the wild
ride that is my life.

22
00:00:45,710 --> 00:00:47,600
Let me take you back to 1985.

23
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:50,010
That's the last time I
walked out of those gates.

24
00:00:50,010 --> 00:00:51,580
I was 16 years old.

25
00:00:51,580 --> 00:00:54,270
I was tall, skinny, and I had ginger hair.

26
00:00:54,270 --> 00:00:56,260
And I was broke, unfortunately,

27
00:00:56,260 --> 00:00:58,784
but I knew I wanted to
make my mark on the world.

28
00:00:58,784 --> 00:01:00,860
And there was no way I could
do that sitting in lessons,

29
00:01:00,860 --> 00:01:03,120
learning about things
I wasn't interested in.

30
00:01:03,120 --> 00:01:04,900
So I went out to seek my fortune.

31
00:01:04,900 --> 00:01:07,873
Before we get there, let me
take you back to my teen years.

32
00:01:07,873 --> 00:01:09,720
I was always looking to make money.

33
00:01:09,720 --> 00:01:12,380
I know it's a little cliche,
but when I was a teen,

34
00:01:12,380 --> 00:01:15,670
my main side hustle was
selling candy and cans of soda

35
00:01:15,670 --> 00:01:17,370
to all the other kids in the playground.

36
00:01:17,370 --> 00:01:19,490
On the weekend, I would also go fishing

37
00:01:19,490 --> 00:01:21,010
and catch hundreds of mackerel,

38
00:01:21,010 --> 00:01:22,790
which I sold around the neighborhood.

39
00:01:22,790 --> 00:01:25,810
I remember knocking on
every single door possible.

40
00:01:25,810 --> 00:01:29,270
I was offering a great
deal, 10 fish for $1.

41
00:01:29,270 --> 00:01:31,720
But unfortunately, no one wanted 10 fish.

42
00:01:31,720 --> 00:01:34,140
so I was forced to go
back to the drawing board

43
00:01:34,140 --> 00:01:36,840
and restructure my business
with a new strategy.

44
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:40,490
I decided, from now on, I'd
be selling five fish for $1,

45
00:01:40,490 --> 00:01:42,490
and I was shocked by the results.

46
00:01:42,490 --> 00:01:43,750
Everyone wanted some.

47
00:01:43,750 --> 00:01:46,520
Looking back now, these
years were so important,

48
00:01:46,520 --> 00:01:49,470
as I was practicing some of
the most important life skills

49
00:01:49,470 --> 00:01:51,660
out there, sales and confidence.

50
00:01:51,660 --> 00:01:52,660
Without these skills,

51
00:01:52,660 --> 00:01:55,050
I don't think I'd have been
able to achieve success

52
00:01:55,050 --> 00:01:55,910
in later life.

53
00:01:55,910 --> 00:01:58,340
So if you just take one
thing from this video,

54
00:01:58,340 --> 00:02:01,120
then it should be to start
honing your sales skills

55
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:02,450
and being confident.

56
00:02:02,450 --> 00:02:04,490
This brings me back to these school gates.

57
00:02:04,490 --> 00:02:07,310
When I left here, I had several
paths that I could follow.

58
00:02:07,310 --> 00:02:09,440
I decided I wanted a nine to five job.

59
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:11,840
I needed to learn a skill
to set me up for life.

60
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:14,800
Going to work at 9:00 AM
and finishing at 5:00 PM

61
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:17,320
was the life that school
had been drilling into me

62
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:18,153
for years.

63
00:02:18,153 --> 00:02:19,840
So I really threw myself into it

64
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:22,170
and actually lined up five different jobs

65
00:02:22,170 --> 00:02:24,240
because I was so keen to be successful.

66
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:27,330
I had the choice between being
a builder, an electrician,

67
00:02:27,330 --> 00:02:29,960
a refrigeration engineer,
a shop assistant,

68
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:31,840
or a carpenter's apprentice.

69
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:34,000
It was a tough decision, but in the end,

70
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:36,040
I decided on becoming a carpenter.

71
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:38,700
The pay wasn't great, around $2 an hour,

72
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:40,160
but I was learning a skill,

73
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:43,150
and I could see the potential
for moving up in the company.

74
00:02:43,150 --> 00:02:45,840
And I really thought that
this was my ticket to success.

75
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:48,560
I really threw myself into
my carpentry apprenticeship,

76
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:50,860
and I learned everything I could.

77
00:02:50,860 --> 00:02:52,730
I even won leadership awards,

78
00:02:52,730 --> 00:02:55,490
and I really felt like I was
moving forward with my life.

79
00:02:55,490 --> 00:02:58,320
I finished my apprenticeship
with honors from the college

80
00:02:58,320 --> 00:02:59,840
and thought, "Here we go.

81
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:01,760
All the big jobs are coming my way."

82
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:04,930
But unfortunately, my managers
seem to take a dislike to me.

83
00:03:04,930 --> 00:03:07,040
Maybe they started to feel
a little bit threatened

84
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:07,980
by my success.

85
00:03:07,980 --> 00:03:11,140
And therefore decided to
give me all the bad jobs.

86
00:03:11,140 --> 00:03:12,050
For months on end,

87
00:03:12,050 --> 00:03:15,410
he assigned me to make wooden
trash cans in the back room.

88
00:03:15,410 --> 00:03:17,470
This gave me no ability to show off

89
00:03:17,470 --> 00:03:18,820
my skills that I'd learned

90
00:03:18,820 --> 00:03:21,490
and prevented me from
working my way up the company

91
00:03:21,490 --> 00:03:22,770
to a higher paid job.

92
00:03:22,770 --> 00:03:23,760
I thought to myself,

93
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:25,810
I hadn't really studied all this time

94
00:03:25,810 --> 00:03:27,450
to make wooden trash cans.

95
00:03:27,450 --> 00:03:30,490
Nowadays, it's the sort of
repetitive job a robot would do.

96
00:03:30,490 --> 00:03:33,030
What was even worse is, when
I looked around the workshop,

97
00:03:33,030 --> 00:03:36,690
I saw many other people doing
lots more interesting jobs.

98
00:03:36,690 --> 00:03:38,390
So I asked to speak to the manager,

99
00:03:38,390 --> 00:03:39,320
and where we're filming,

100
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:41,850
this is the exact spot where we stood.

101
00:03:41,850 --> 00:03:43,610
I said I needed more of a challenge.

102
00:03:43,610 --> 00:03:45,160
I couldn't keep making these bins.

103
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:46,610
And you know what he said to me?

104
00:03:46,610 --> 00:03:48,180
He said, "You're making these bins today.

105
00:03:48,180 --> 00:03:49,710
You'll be making these bins tomorrow.

106
00:03:49,710 --> 00:03:52,250
We've got a five-year
contract with Walmart.

107
00:03:52,250 --> 00:03:54,170
You're gonna be making
a lot of these bins."

108
00:03:54,170 --> 00:03:57,250
Now, that's when I realized
I was completely powerless

109
00:03:57,250 --> 00:03:58,760
working a nine to five job

110
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:00,810
at the mercy of whoever was in charge.

111
00:04:00,810 --> 00:04:02,980
The pay was only just
enough to cover my bills,

112
00:04:02,980 --> 00:04:04,800
which meant I couldn't just quit,

113
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:07,250
but I was also unable to save any money.

114
00:04:07,250 --> 00:04:08,880
I was essentially trapped.

115
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:10,910
So I got a Saturday job working

116
00:04:10,910 --> 00:04:12,530
in a radio-controlled model shop.

117
00:04:12,530 --> 00:04:15,310
I also started a side
hustle flipping cars,

118
00:04:15,310 --> 00:04:18,480
which basically consisted
of finding underpriced cars,

119
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:21,150
fixing them up, and then
selling them for a profit.

120
00:04:21,150 --> 00:04:25,210
To this day, I still own
this Ford Fiesta XR-2 Mark 1.

121
00:04:25,210 --> 00:04:27,050
It's a 1985 model.

122
00:04:27,050 --> 00:04:28,910
And the cars I was buying at that stage

123
00:04:28,910 --> 00:04:31,280
would cost me two to $300.

124
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:35,560
And I was usually flipping
them for, I'd say, 500 to $600.

125
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:36,850
This little beauty is worth

126
00:04:36,850 --> 00:04:38,180
a little bit more than that now though.

127
00:04:38,180 --> 00:04:39,400
As well as doing all of this,

128
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:41,140
I was also teaching people to fly

129
00:04:41,140 --> 00:04:43,090
radio-controlled helicopters on Sunday.

130
00:04:43,090 --> 00:04:45,200
There was a huge demand at the time.

131
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:47,470
And all Sunday, I will be booked out

132
00:04:47,470 --> 00:04:48,870
as long as the weather was good,

133
00:04:48,870 --> 00:04:50,460
having these multiple side hustles

134
00:04:50,460 --> 00:04:53,810
allowed me to finally build out
some kind of emergency fund.

135
00:04:53,810 --> 00:04:55,010
This is so important.

136
00:04:55,010 --> 00:04:57,120
It gives you the freedom to take advantage

137
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:59,680
of any opportunities that come your way

138
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:02,090
without having to worry
about paying your bills.

139
00:05:02,090 --> 00:05:03,790
There is a huge opportunity cost

140
00:05:03,790 --> 00:05:06,300
that comes from living
paycheck to paycheck,

141
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:09,000
as you're so focused on next month's wage

142
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,470
that you end up going through life

143
00:05:10,470 --> 00:05:11,960
with your eyes half-closed

144
00:05:11,960 --> 00:05:13,920
and passing up on many opportunities

145
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:14,980
without even knowing it.

146
00:05:14,980 --> 00:05:15,840
One day at work,

147
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:18,160
the boss asked if anyone wanted to help

148
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:21,180
install this beautiful
staircase at a customer's house.

149
00:05:21,180 --> 00:05:22,810
I jumped at the chance.

150
00:05:22,810 --> 00:05:26,250
It was one of the most impressive
houses that I'd ever seen.

151
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:27,340
It had everything.

152
00:05:27,340 --> 00:05:30,410
I'm talking marble floors, chandeliers,

153
00:05:30,410 --> 00:05:31,960
a private swimming pool,

154
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:35,260
and a garage full of
beautiful sports cars.

155
00:05:35,260 --> 00:05:36,800
It was my dream house.

156
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:39,700
I started daydreaming and
adding up how many years

157
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:41,420
it would take me to earn enough money

158
00:05:41,420 --> 00:05:42,917
to buy a place like this.

159
00:05:42,917 --> 00:05:46,350
And I got gradually more
and more demoralized,

160
00:05:46,350 --> 00:05:48,410
as even with all my side hustles,

161
00:05:48,410 --> 00:05:51,210
I realized I still would
never have enough money.

162
00:05:51,210 --> 00:05:54,650
It was so close, but just
so far at the same time.

163
00:05:54,650 --> 00:05:56,980
And I felt there's really
nothing more I could do

164
00:05:56,980 --> 00:05:57,950
to achieve it.

165
00:05:57,950 --> 00:06:01,430
I was absolutely exhausted,
physically and mentally.

166
00:06:01,430 --> 00:06:03,860
I was working every hour of every day.

167
00:06:03,860 --> 00:06:05,230
While installing the staircase,

168
00:06:05,230 --> 00:06:06,720
I would often look out the window

169
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:09,040
and see the owner relaxing in the garden,

170
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,750
or going off to play golf.

171
00:06:10,750 --> 00:06:12,210
And I really couldn't understand

172
00:06:12,210 --> 00:06:15,260
how this guy managed to
have the life that he wanted

173
00:06:15,260 --> 00:06:17,180
and go and have fun whenever he wished.

174
00:06:17,180 --> 00:06:19,220
So I had to ask him a few questions,

175
00:06:19,220 --> 00:06:21,910
and he told me all about
how running his business

176
00:06:21,910 --> 00:06:24,690
gave him the ability to
make money while he slept.

177
00:06:24,690 --> 00:06:27,810
This is when I first
discovered passive income.

178
00:06:27,810 --> 00:06:29,770
I'd never thought this was
really possible for me,

179
00:06:29,770 --> 00:06:32,870
as school had only ever taught
me one way of making money,

180
00:06:32,870 --> 00:06:34,710
and that was working a normal job.

181
00:06:34,710 --> 00:06:38,610
This concept of making passive
income was so alien to me,

182
00:06:38,610 --> 00:06:41,100
but it really got the
wheels turning in my mind.

183
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:44,620
If this was a normal guy and
he was able to do all this,

184
00:06:44,620 --> 00:06:46,650
then I was pretty sure
that I could do it too.

185
00:06:46,650 --> 00:06:48,570
I started thinking back to my school years

186
00:06:48,570 --> 00:06:49,770
and selling those fish.

187
00:06:49,770 --> 00:06:51,590
That was my first real experience

188
00:06:51,590 --> 00:06:53,010
of running a small business.

189
00:06:53,010 --> 00:06:54,920
And I'd loved every second of it,

190
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:57,090
from sourcing to selling the product.

191
00:06:57,090 --> 00:07:00,190
I couldn't believe that I'd
been suppressing this for years

192
00:07:00,190 --> 00:07:03,410
and trying to conform to
what society wanted me to do.

193
00:07:03,410 --> 00:07:05,650
Nowadays, "passive income" has become

194
00:07:05,650 --> 00:07:07,670
a bit of a buzzword on the internet,

195
00:07:07,670 --> 00:07:09,960
and I don't completely
agree with the term,

196
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:11,850
as it can sound a little misleading.

197
00:07:11,850 --> 00:07:14,140
Kickstarting a passive
income is certainly not

198
00:07:14,140 --> 00:07:15,330
an easy thing to do,

199
00:07:15,330 --> 00:07:17,980
but the idea is that you
can do something once,

200
00:07:17,980 --> 00:07:20,860
like setting up a business
or investing some money,

201
00:07:20,860 --> 00:07:23,280
and then earn from it even
when you're not working.

202
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:25,100
Of course, this requires some maintenance,

203
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:26,060
but in my opinion,

204
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:27,530
it's a better way to make money

205
00:07:27,530 --> 00:07:29,030
than working a nine to five job

206
00:07:29,030 --> 00:07:31,120
if you want to be successful
when you're younger,

207
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:32,410
as your time is limited,

208
00:07:32,410 --> 00:07:34,510
and therefore, your income is capped.

209
00:07:34,510 --> 00:07:36,980
Now I knew that passive
income was the answer.

210
00:07:36,980 --> 00:07:39,050
I devised a plan of escape.

211
00:07:39,050 --> 00:07:40,940
To have the best chance of success,

212
00:07:40,940 --> 00:07:44,130
I knew it was important to
create a business in an industry

213
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:47,450
that I was both familiar with
and also passionate about.

214
00:07:47,450 --> 00:07:48,490
And I was lucky.

215
00:07:48,490 --> 00:07:50,090
I had the perfect idea.

216
00:07:50,090 --> 00:07:52,010
The shop I was working in on Saturdays

217
00:07:52,010 --> 00:07:53,790
was a radio-controlled model store.

218
00:07:53,790 --> 00:07:55,530
Over the years that
I'd been working there,

219
00:07:55,530 --> 00:07:58,430
I spotted lots of things they
could be doing differently

220
00:07:58,430 --> 00:08:00,540
and all the mistakes
that they were making,

221
00:08:00,540 --> 00:08:03,680
I researched and found the
perfect location for a store.

222
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:05,460
I even came up with the perfect name,

223
00:08:05,460 --> 00:08:07,840
which was inspired by an old TV show

224
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:10,630
I used to watch when I was
younger, "Model World."

225
00:08:10,630 --> 00:08:12,580
I could really see the
potential with this shop

226
00:08:12,580 --> 00:08:14,200
and how it would eventually operate

227
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:15,820
without me even having to be there,

228
00:08:15,820 --> 00:08:17,960
essentially creating passive income.

229
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:20,000
It finally gave me some hope and direction

230
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,760
while I was working my normal job,

231
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:25,150
as I knew that it was now
only a temporary situation.

232
00:08:25,150 --> 00:08:27,900
Unfortunately, not a lot
of people believed in me.

233
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:30,080
I came from a working class background,

234
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:32,340
and I had little to no qualifications,

235
00:08:32,340 --> 00:08:35,100
so no one thought I'd be able
to break into the market,

236
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:39,310
except for one of my friends,
who I told my entire plan to.

237
00:08:39,310 --> 00:08:42,120
I couldn't wait to quit
my job and get started,

238
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,940
so I could prove everyone wrong.

239
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:46,860
I just needed to get enough
money together first.

240
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:50,050
Within a few months, Model
World Shop was up and running,

241
00:08:50,050 --> 00:08:51,720
but it was nothing to do with me.

242
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:54,950
My friend had stolen my
idea and done it himself.

243
00:08:54,950 --> 00:08:57,020
I felt so betrayed and frustrated

244
00:08:57,020 --> 00:08:59,440
that I'd trusted him with all my plans.

245
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:01,380
I even started thinking to myself

246
00:09:01,380 --> 00:09:03,490
that maybe being an entrepreneur

247
00:09:03,490 --> 00:09:04,850
wasn't actually right for me.

248
00:09:04,850 --> 00:09:06,710
I was stuck in my nine to five job,

249
00:09:06,710 --> 00:09:08,710
being ordered around by my manager,

250
00:09:08,710 --> 00:09:10,740
with every bit of hope shattered.

251
00:09:10,740 --> 00:09:13,610
The worst part was watching
my friend living my dream.

252
00:09:13,610 --> 00:09:16,720
I felt like a sprinter chained
up in the starting blocks,

253
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:18,710
unable to release all that energy.

254
00:09:18,710 --> 00:09:20,860
It was one of the worst
feelings in my life.

255
00:09:20,860 --> 00:09:22,700
The whole future I built in my head

256
00:09:22,700 --> 00:09:24,570
started to come crashing down.

257
00:09:24,570 --> 00:09:27,000
Looking back, this was a
great life lesson for me,

258
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:29,130
although I didn't see it
like that at the time.

259
00:09:29,130 --> 00:09:30,370
If you have a great idea,

260
00:09:30,370 --> 00:09:32,720
then it's best to operate in the shadows.

261
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:35,800
Maybe tell parts of your
plans to different people,

262
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:38,360
but don't give the whole
game away like I did.

263
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:39,800
After the huge setback,

264
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:43,060
I decided to pick myself
up and keep working.

265
00:09:43,060 --> 00:09:44,770
I grinded as hard as I could

266
00:09:44,770 --> 00:09:46,330
and bought my first apartment

267
00:09:46,330 --> 00:09:47,870
to build up my credit score.

268
00:09:47,870 --> 00:09:49,730
I thought I was working hard before,

269
00:09:49,730 --> 00:09:51,900
but this was really the next level.

270
00:09:51,900 --> 00:09:53,650
I worked every hour under the sun,

271
00:09:53,650 --> 00:09:56,270
as I wasn't gonna let
my financial situation

272
00:09:56,270 --> 00:09:59,370
leave me open to having my
dreams taken away from me again.

273
00:09:59,370 --> 00:10:01,710
This just shows the path to passive income

274
00:10:01,710 --> 00:10:03,300
is by no means easy.

275
00:10:03,300 --> 00:10:05,720
There can be a lot of
setbacks along the way,

276
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:07,110
but if you stay focused,

277
00:10:07,110 --> 00:10:09,530
then opportunities will
present themselves.

278
00:10:09,530 --> 00:10:11,050
As if by magic, one day,

279
00:10:11,050 --> 00:10:13,420
I heard some great news that my friend

280
00:10:13,420 --> 00:10:15,030
wanted to sell Model World.

281
00:10:15,030 --> 00:10:16,420
I'd visited a few times

282
00:10:16,420 --> 00:10:17,840
and noticed that he wasn't giving it

283
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:19,200
the attention it needed.

284
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:21,010
It had huge potential,

285
00:10:21,010 --> 00:10:23,220
but his passions were not in the business.

286
00:10:23,220 --> 00:10:24,860
I knew I needed to buy the shop

287
00:10:24,860 --> 00:10:26,900
and get my dreams back on track.

288
00:10:26,900 --> 00:10:30,270
This was the opportunity that
I'd been preparing myself for,

289
00:10:30,270 --> 00:10:32,500
and I wasn't gonna let it
slip from my fingers again.

290
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:34,510
I had a little bit of money behind me,

291
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:36,100
but it still wasn't gonna be enough,

292
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:37,950
nowhere near enough.

293
00:10:37,950 --> 00:10:39,820
But I'd built up a good credit score,

294
00:10:39,820 --> 00:10:41,700
so I thought, "I know what.

295
00:10:41,700 --> 00:10:43,370
I'll leverage the money I had

296
00:10:43,370 --> 00:10:44,890
and see if I can get a bank loan."

297
00:10:44,890 --> 00:10:47,780
He'd taken my great
idea, he'd taken my name,

298
00:10:47,780 --> 00:10:50,710
but the one thing he couldn't
take from me was my passion.

299
00:10:50,710 --> 00:10:52,900
And I knew that was the secret ingredient

300
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:54,040
to making this business

301
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:57,060
a great passive income-generating machine.

302
00:10:57,060 --> 00:10:59,460
So I created the best
business plan I could

303
00:10:59,460 --> 00:11:01,000
and got a meeting with the bank.

304
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,610
I'd banked there since I was a kid,

305
00:11:02,610 --> 00:11:04,130
and I had a good credit score,

306
00:11:04,130 --> 00:11:06,620
so I was hoping that
everything would go smoothly.

307
00:11:06,620 --> 00:11:09,280
Within 10 minutes, I'd
been denied the loan.

308
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:11,620
It was the worst interview of my life.

309
00:11:11,620 --> 00:11:13,990
Oh, it felt like I've been
kicked out of the bank.

310
00:11:13,990 --> 00:11:14,990
It was unreal.

311
00:11:14,990 --> 00:11:16,180
My head was down.

312
00:11:16,180 --> 00:11:17,910
I was walking back to my car

313
00:11:17,910 --> 00:11:18,743
Do you know what?

314
00:11:18,743 --> 00:11:19,710
I really didn't know what to do.

315
00:11:19,710 --> 00:11:21,640
It was like being back
at that house again,

316
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:23,840
so close yet so far.

317
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:26,210
I had to pick myself up,
and as luck would have it,

318
00:11:26,210 --> 00:11:29,280
the next building I stumbled
on was this bank here.

319
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:31,710
I hustled my way in, and I got a meeting,

320
00:11:31,710 --> 00:11:34,040
right there and then, with the manager.

321
00:11:34,040 --> 00:11:36,860
He actually said it was
a very interesting idea

322
00:11:36,860 --> 00:11:38,320
and not only gave me the loan,

323
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:40,810
but promised to be one
of my first customers.

324
00:11:40,810 --> 00:11:43,860
I have since asked him what
made him take a chance on me,

325
00:11:43,860 --> 00:11:46,440
and he said he was
always eager to help out

326
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:47,800
the younger generation,

327
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:50,580
and when he saw how passionate
and hard-working I was,

328
00:11:50,580 --> 00:11:51,940
he just couldn't say no.

329
00:11:51,940 --> 00:11:53,520
This is a perfect example

330
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:57,350
of where preparation and
resilience meets opportunity.

331
00:11:57,350 --> 00:11:59,200
You never know when
your next stroke of luck

332
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,370
is around the corner.

333
00:12:00,370 --> 00:12:03,670
And for me, it quite literally
was just around the corner.

334
00:12:03,670 --> 00:12:06,880
So without any hesitation, I
closed the deal on Model World,

335
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:09,800
the rights to the name and
all the products they had.

336
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:11,260
It was finally mine.

337
00:12:11,260 --> 00:12:14,510
I knew the hard work was yet
to come, but it was mine.

338
00:12:14,510 --> 00:12:16,030
The first day I opened the shop,

339
00:12:16,030 --> 00:12:18,150
I had a sleeping bag behind the counter

340
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:20,950
because I knew, if I didn't
make enough money that day,

341
00:12:20,950 --> 00:12:22,090
I'd be sleeping there

342
00:12:22,090 --> 00:12:23,640
because I certainly didn't have enough gas

343
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:24,890
to drive the car home.

344
00:12:24,890 --> 00:12:27,330
Luckily, the first day
was a great success.

345
00:12:27,330 --> 00:12:29,320
All the selling and negotiation skills

346
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:32,370
I'd learned when I was
younger came in really useful.

347
00:12:32,370 --> 00:12:33,203
Without them,

348
00:12:33,203 --> 00:12:35,770
I wouldn't have been able to
make my business profitable.

349
00:12:35,770 --> 00:12:38,680
After three years, we turned
over a million dollars,

350
00:12:38,680 --> 00:12:39,710
and it was crazy.

351
00:12:39,710 --> 00:12:43,220
It was crazy times, but
it was good fun times.

352
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:45,650
And we had more challenges along the way.

353
00:12:45,650 --> 00:12:46,650
After 10 years,

354
00:12:46,650 --> 00:12:50,140
we had three shops and a
warehouse stuffed full of gear.

355
00:12:50,140 --> 00:12:51,660
But we wanted to be number one,

356
00:12:51,660 --> 00:12:54,100
so we had plans to push on even more.

357
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:56,680
I was generating millions
in passive income,

358
00:12:56,680 --> 00:12:58,830
and I felt like I'd finally made it,

359
00:12:58,830 --> 00:13:01,070
but I didn't realize just how open I was

360
00:13:01,070 --> 00:13:02,750
to losing everything.

361
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:04,500
When it seems to be going amazingly well,

362
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:07,010
you can start to get a little complacent,

363
00:13:07,010 --> 00:13:09,550
as it seems like nothing
can stand in your way.

364
00:13:09,550 --> 00:13:10,790
This is really dangerous,

365
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:13,730
as you stop innovating and
take your eye off the ball.

366
00:13:13,730 --> 00:13:16,550
I was so heavily focused
on one stream of income

367
00:13:16,550 --> 00:13:17,780
from my retail shops

368
00:13:17,780 --> 00:13:19,530
that when internet shopping struck,

369
00:13:19,530 --> 00:13:22,140
I was completely taken by surprise.

370
00:13:22,140 --> 00:13:24,080
It was really sink or swim.

371
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:26,820
Everyone I knew was getting
wiped out of business,

372
00:13:26,820 --> 00:13:28,500
and I knew it was only a matter of time

373
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:30,350
before that was gonna happen to me

374
00:13:30,350 --> 00:13:32,660
if I didn't quickly adapt to the times.

375
00:13:32,660 --> 00:13:34,690
Luckily, I had a little longer than most

376
00:13:34,690 --> 00:13:36,710
because I'd been investing
in the stock market

377
00:13:36,710 --> 00:13:38,400
and real estate from a young age.

378
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:39,810
If I didn't have these assets,

379
00:13:39,810 --> 00:13:41,510
then I would've probably gone bankrupt.

380
00:13:41,510 --> 00:13:43,080
By the way, if you're in the USA,

381
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,970
then Public is giving away a free stock

382
00:13:44,970 --> 00:13:46,800
worth all the way up to a hundred dollars.

383
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:48,070
I'll leave the link below.

384
00:13:48,070 --> 00:13:49,110
And if you're in the UK,

385
00:13:49,110 --> 00:13:51,160
then Free Trade has
given away a free stock

386
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:52,980
worth all the way up to 200 pounds.

387
00:13:52,980 --> 00:13:54,580
I'll leave that link down there too.

388
00:13:54,580 --> 00:13:56,110
I wish I'd had them when I was younger.

389
00:13:56,110 --> 00:13:58,600
While lots of people saw
the internet as the problem,

390
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:00,590
I also saw it as the solution,

391
00:14:00,590 --> 00:14:03,200
as it gave me the ability
to reach far more people

392
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:05,920
than I ever could before,
even while I was sleeping.

393
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:08,720
So instead of focusing my
efforts on building more shops,

394
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:11,300
I decided to create a
big central location,

395
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:12,850
complete with warehouses,

396
00:14:12,850 --> 00:14:15,970
which could be used to serve
customers all over the world,

397
00:14:15,970 --> 00:14:17,850
instead of just in my local area.

398
00:14:17,850 --> 00:14:20,150
But I knew that if I
wanted to protect myself

399
00:14:20,150 --> 00:14:22,340
from something like this
happening in the future,

400
00:14:22,340 --> 00:14:24,060
then adapting wouldn't be enough.

401
00:14:24,060 --> 00:14:26,890
I need to create more
passive income streams,

402
00:14:26,890 --> 00:14:29,230
so I wasn't just balancing my life on one.

403
00:14:29,230 --> 00:14:32,170
My passive income streams
has always been B2C,

404
00:14:32,170 --> 00:14:35,150
meaning I sold from my
business to my customers,

405
00:14:35,150 --> 00:14:36,760
but I had always had the idea

406
00:14:36,760 --> 00:14:39,930
of starting a business that
sold to other businesses,

407
00:14:39,930 --> 00:14:42,830
which will create an entirely
different income source.

408
00:14:42,830 --> 00:14:44,110
I happened to know someone

409
00:14:44,110 --> 00:14:46,200
who had a similar business out in America.

410
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:48,410
So me and my girlfriend,
she's now the wife,

411
00:14:48,410 --> 00:14:51,858
packed our bags and took
a spontaneous trip to LA.

412
00:14:51,858 --> 00:14:54,441
(upbeat music)

413
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:01,810
The trip was so unplanned

414
00:15:01,810 --> 00:15:04,000
that I even forgot my driving license,

415
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,370
so when we landed at LAX Airport,

416
00:15:06,370 --> 00:15:10,130
I had to go to the most dodgy
car rental place in history.

417
00:15:10,130 --> 00:15:13,660
All I managed to rent was this
old Dodge Dynasty town car,

418
00:15:13,660 --> 00:15:15,000
which was falling apart.

419
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:16,060
Then, following the map,

420
00:15:16,060 --> 00:15:18,540
we drove that baby all
the way up the coast road

421
00:15:18,540 --> 00:15:19,730
to San Francisco.

422
00:15:19,730 --> 00:15:21,630
That's where the guy I
wanted to meet lived,

423
00:15:21,630 --> 00:15:24,850
in a small town called
Milpitas, just near San Jose.

424
00:15:24,850 --> 00:15:27,710
I didn't even have a hotel
booked, so we just winged it.

425
00:15:27,710 --> 00:15:29,317
And as the song goes, I thought,

426
00:15:29,317 --> 00:15:32,090
"You'll always find a room
at the Hotel California."

427
00:15:32,090 --> 00:15:34,750
However, it turned out to
be a big convention week.

428
00:15:34,750 --> 00:15:36,660
There wasn't a room to be had.

429
00:15:36,660 --> 00:15:39,110
We ended up in the most dodgy motel

430
00:15:39,110 --> 00:15:41,130
I'd ever stayed in in my life.

431
00:15:41,130 --> 00:15:42,840
We didn't even risk getting undressed.

432
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:44,440
We just slept on top of the bed

433
00:15:44,440 --> 00:15:46,530
in case we had to get out fast.

434
00:15:46,530 --> 00:15:48,020
It was just one of those things.

435
00:15:48,020 --> 00:15:50,230
He was very shocked to
see us when we arrived,

436
00:15:50,230 --> 00:15:52,200
as he had no idea I was coming.

437
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:54,560
I just rolled up, knocked
on the door, and said,

438
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:56,030
"I was just passing."

439
00:15:56,030 --> 00:15:58,830
He said, "That's one hell
of a road trip from the UK."

440
00:15:58,830 --> 00:16:00,563
He then helped me
structure my new business,

441
00:16:00,563 --> 00:16:03,870
and, in return, I agreed to
stock some of his products.

442
00:16:03,870 --> 00:16:06,310
I knew that if I wanted to
sell to other businesses,

443
00:16:06,310 --> 00:16:09,350
then I need to build out my
own unique product range.

444
00:16:09,350 --> 00:16:12,240
My experience as a carpenter
came in really handy

445
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:13,750
when designing my products.

446
00:16:13,750 --> 00:16:16,180
Now, all that was left was
getting them mass-produced,

447
00:16:16,180 --> 00:16:19,030
so I decided to travel
to Shanghai in China

448
00:16:19,030 --> 00:16:20,230
to find a factory.

449
00:16:20,230 --> 00:16:21,170
Before I knew it,

450
00:16:21,170 --> 00:16:23,930
I'd been interviewed at the
Chinese embassy in London,

451
00:16:23,930 --> 00:16:25,300
issued with a visa,

452
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:28,460
and I sat on a plane with
a few faxes printed out.

453
00:16:28,460 --> 00:16:30,357
And they said on the top of these faxes,

454
00:16:30,357 --> 00:16:33,460
"Hand this to the taxi driver
when you get to the airport."

455
00:16:33,460 --> 00:16:34,940
I couldn't read the rest of it

456
00:16:34,940 --> 00:16:37,330
because it was all in Chinese characters.

457
00:16:37,330 --> 00:16:40,090
I could have quite
literally ended up anywhere.

458
00:16:40,090 --> 00:16:42,030
The trip went really, really well,

459
00:16:42,030 --> 00:16:44,160
and I gained lots of new contacts

460
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:46,220
with many invites to travel to Shenzhen

461
00:16:46,220 --> 00:16:48,020
to visit their factories.

462
00:16:48,020 --> 00:16:49,730
I still think that if you take the trouble

463
00:16:49,730 --> 00:16:51,170
to meet people for real,

464
00:16:51,170 --> 00:16:53,390
then you can grow a real bond in business

465
00:16:53,390 --> 00:16:54,770
where you help each other.

466
00:16:54,770 --> 00:16:57,660
You have to press the
flesh to gain that loyalty,

467
00:16:57,660 --> 00:17:00,820
and that's why politicians
always wanna shake your hand

468
00:17:00,820 --> 00:17:03,950
because it's almost like a
contract to secure your vote.

469
00:17:03,950 --> 00:17:05,370
That brings me to today.

470
00:17:05,370 --> 00:17:07,050
My businesses are thriving,

471
00:17:07,050 --> 00:17:09,970
and my passive income streams
are stronger than ever.

472
00:17:09,970 --> 00:17:11,300
One of the most important things

473
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:12,760
I've learned from my experience

474
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:14,380
is that there is less risk

475
00:17:14,380 --> 00:17:17,380
in stepping out of your
comfort zone and adapting

476
00:17:17,380 --> 00:17:19,850
than there is in not
taking any risk at all.

477
00:17:19,850 --> 00:17:21,830
If you've been considering
quitting your job,

478
00:17:21,830 --> 00:17:22,950
then know this.

479
00:17:22,950 --> 00:17:26,080
If you've got the right plan
and the right motivation,

480
00:17:26,080 --> 00:17:29,200
you have as much chance
of success as anyone else.

481
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:31,380
You don't have to come from a rich family.

482
00:17:31,380 --> 00:17:33,490
You don't have to have
lots of connections.

483
00:17:33,490 --> 00:17:35,760
The barriers to entry
in the business world

484
00:17:35,760 --> 00:17:37,220
have never been this low.

485
00:17:37,220 --> 00:17:39,920
All you need is a computer, some brains...

486
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:41,270
That certainly helps.

487
00:17:41,270 --> 00:17:42,630
And an internet connection

488
00:17:42,630 --> 00:17:44,920
to make your first bit of startup money.

489
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:45,753
Who knows?

490
00:17:45,753 --> 00:17:47,840
One day, you could be
sitting in the boss's seat

491
00:17:47,840 --> 00:17:49,510
behind the boss's desk.

492
00:17:49,510 --> 00:17:52,170
And this is literally the boss's desk.

493
00:17:52,170 --> 00:17:54,540
I was once sitting just where you are now,

494
00:17:54,540 --> 00:17:57,130
having my interview to become a carpenter.

495
00:17:57,130 --> 00:17:59,200
When that firm went into receivership

496
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:00,700
and it came up for auction,

497
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:03,410
I went straight down there,
and I bought this desk.

498
00:18:03,410 --> 00:18:05,130
So I'm gonna leave the
next video up there,

499
00:18:05,130 --> 00:18:07,000
but don't click on it just yet.

